This particular CD is a slight departure from their usually foul-for-the-sake-of-being-foul lyrics, the tracks are thought provoking with titles like: `Cocaine, OIL, Freedom, Credit, Baghdad', in fact the CD's title itself `Bread' is a theme for the songs.

If you are familiar with SKA and SKA-PUNK you will be very much at home with those track no matter what language they are sung in. If you don't know the genre, then about time you have tried it, and Leningrad are as good an introduction as any.
